    <stitle>RADIATOR/COOLING SYSTEM SERVICE MANUAL - PROSTAR&#8482; - COOLING PACKAGE COMPONENTS - FAN BELT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>FAN BELT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan Belt - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202141" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202141.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. New Cummins Belt Tensioner</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. NEW BELT TENSIONER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TENSIONER RELEASE HOLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A new engine belt tensioner is available on the ProStar&#8482;. An extra release hole has been
                        added in the new design to aid in service of the fan belt.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1202111" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202111.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Fan Belt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FAN BELT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FAN DRIVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TENSIONER RELEASE HOLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BELT TENSIONER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert ratchet in belt tensioner release hole, relieve tension from fan belt, and remove
                    fan belt from belt tensioner.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fan belt from all pulleys.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fan belt, by working the fan belt around the radiator fan.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan Belt - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Manual re-tensioning is not needed on belts equipped with a spring-loaded automatic belt
                        tensioner.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect the fan belt for damage and wear prior to installation. The fan belt should be
                        replaced if any defects are found.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install fan belt, by working the fan belt around the radiator fan.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position fan belt on all pulleys except belt tensioner (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202111">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert ratchet in belt tensioner release hole, relieve tension from tensioner, and
                    install fan belt on belt tensioner (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202111">Figure 16, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
